Before a vinification can be released, every output product that requires lot tracking must
have its full output quantity distributed across one or more **lot numbers**. The
**Lot Assignment** window guides you through this.

## When does it appear?

The Lot Assignment window opens automatically as part of the **Release** action when one or more output items require lot numbers. You assign the lots, confirm, and the release continues.

## The Lot Assignment window

The window has two parts:

- An upper list of **output items** that need lot numbers.
- A lower **Lot No. Lines** part where you enter the lot numbers and quantities for the
  selected item.

### Output items list

| Field | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| **Item No.** | The output item requiring lot number assignment. |
| **Item Description** | Description of the output item. |
| **Output Quantity** | Total quantity to be produced that must be fully covered by lot assignments. |
| **Qty. Assigned** | Total quantity already distributed across lot numbers for this item. |
| **Remaining Quantity** | Quantity still to be assigned. It is highlighted while not zero. |

> The **Remaining Quantity** must be **zero for every item** before you can confirm.

### Lot No. Lines

For the currently selected output item, add one line per lot number:

| Field | What to enter |
|-------|---------------|
| **Lot No.** | The lot number for this portion of the output. Use the assist-edit (…) button to generate one automatically (see below). |
| **Qty. to Handle** | The quantity assigned to this lot number. The sum of all lines must equal the Output Quantity. |

The totals at the bottom of the Lot No. Lines part show:

- **Output Quantity** — total to distribute.
- **Quantity Handled** — sum assigned so far.
- **Remaining Quantity** — still unassigned (must reach zero).

## Generating a lot number automatically

1. On a Lot No. line, choose the assist-edit (…) button in the **Lot No.** field.
2. Confirm the prompt to generate a lot number from the item configuration.
3. The system generates the lot number using:
   - the item's **Lot No. Formula** (EOS WINE formula), if defined; otherwise
   - the item's **Lot Nos.** number series.
4. If the lot number does not yet exist, the corresponding **Lot No. Information** record is
   created automatically.

If neither a formula nor a number series is configured on the item, type the lot number
manually.

> Each lot number must be unique within the assignment — assigning the same lot twice is
> rejected.

## Confirming

When the **Remaining Quantity** is zero for all output items, choose **Confirm**. The window
closes and the release proceeds. If you cancel instead, the release is aborted and the
document stays in *Processing*.

## Output item lot numbers on the card

The output **… Lot No.** fields in the **Items** group of the Vinification card show the lot
assigned to each single-lot output. For outputs split across several lots, the detailed
distribution is managed through this Lot Assignment window during release.